summary: |
  Wave 5 ships integrator-pass (surgical ROADMAP.md edits from resolved
  open_questions), stall detector (dimensionSnapshot comparison + no-resolve
  guard), and pass-cap halt. FC-05 retire-dimension auto-resolves orphan
  questions in same atomic state write. INTEGRATOR_NO_ENVELOPE rejects
  non-envelope returns. Driver wires all three behaviors with deterministic
  ordering: auto-resolve → integrator → stall → pass-cap.

keyDecisions[4]:
  Auto-resolve runs BEFORE integrator-pass so integrator skips dimension-archived questions
  Stall checked AFTER integrator-pass — resolved questions on same pass prevent false stalls
  Pass-cap checked after stall — stall wins if both conditions hold (correctness over completeness signaling)
  Surgical edits insert resolution block after matching section heading; untouched sections preserved byte-for-byte

